Method for distinguishing methamphetamine from N-isopropylamine

Abstract
translated from

The invention discloses a method for distinguishing methamphetamine from N-isopropylamine, which has the advantages of strong specificity, high separation degree, high precision, stability, good reproducibility, high recovery rate and accurate result, can simultaneously carry out qualitative and quantitative analysis on the two compounds, can effectively distinguish the methamphetamine and the isomer N-isopropylamine thereof in the actual case analysis related to the qualitative and quantitative analysis of ice toxicity, and has important significance for judging and controlling case properties.

Description
translated from Chinese

6N-
N-A kind of method of distinguishing methamphetamine and N-isopropylbenzylamine

technical field

N-N-The invention relates to a method for distinguishing methamphetamine and N-isopropylbenzylamine, in particular to a method for analyzing methamphetamine and N-isopropylbenzylamine by high-performance liquid chromatography in series with mass spectrometry.

Background technique

(metianphetamineMA)C10H15N149.23N-(N-IsopropylbenzylamineN-IBA)Metianphetamine (MA) is the first class of psychoactive drugs strictly controlled by the state. It has a central nervous system stimulant effect and is highly addictive. Its molecular formula is C 10 H 15 N, its molecular weight is 149.23, and it is colorless at room temperature. Oily liquid, its hydrochloride is white crystal or white powder. When the purity is not high, the appearance is large crystal, which is similar to ice. Therefore, it is commonly known as "ice" and is currently the most frequently seized variety in drug crimes. N-Isopropylbenzylamine (N-IBA) is an isomer of methamphetamine with the following structural formula:

N-N-(2016.4.11)N-At room temperature, it is a colorless or light yellow transparent liquid, and its physical properties are very close to methamphetamine. The appearance of the hydrochloride of the two is very similar, so in recent years N-isopropylbenzylamine hydrochloride is often used in the adulteration and counterfeiting of "ice", commonly known as "fake methamphetamine" or thinner. The current research has not found that N-isopropylbenzylamine has a stimulant effect and is not addictive, so it does not belong to the state-controlled species. According to the "Criminal Law of the People's Republic of China" and the "Interpretation of the Supreme People's Court on Several Issues Concerning the Application of Law in the Trial of Drug Crime Cases" (implemented on April 11, 2016), in drug crime cases, the amount of drugs is directly related to the sentencing, while One of methamphetamine and N-isopropylbenzylamine is a controlled drug and the other is a non-controlled chemical raw material, but they are easily confused during detection, resulting in false positives and increased sample content. Therefore, the two are clearly distinguished and quantitatively analyzed. , which is of great significance to the determination and sentencing of the nature of the case.

N-N-N-From the current research, it is difficult to distinguish methamphetamine and N-isopropylbenzylamine by infrared spectroscopy and methamphetamine detection test paper. Gas chromatography-mass spectrometry can effectively distinguish between the two at higher concentrations. However, when the sample matrix is complex, there are often many interferences, making it difficult to identify the two, and at low concentrations, it is also difficult to identify; HPLC can effectively separate methamphetamine and N-isopropylbenzylamine , but due to its weak qualitative ability, it is lacking in the evidence map in forensic science; high performance liquid chromatography tandem mass spectrometry is a qualitative and quantitative analysis method recognized by forensic science, and this method is used for methamphetamine and N-isopropyl Reports on the separation and analysis of benzylamine are rare.

SUMMARY OF THE INVENTION

N-The purpose of this invention is to provide a kind of methamphetamine and N-isopropylbenzylamine high performance liquid chromatography tandem mass spectrometry analysis method, can carry out qualitative and quantitative analysis to both simultaneously.

The technical scheme adopted by the present invention is:

N-A method for distinguishing methamphetamine and N-isopropylbenzylamine, the method comprises the steps:

1)1) Prepare the test sample solution;

2)2) inject the test sample solution into the high performance liquid chromatography tandem mass spectrometer for measurement, select the characteristic ion pair and characteristic fragment ion, compare the retention time, characteristic ion pair, characteristic ion pair of the test sample and standard sample chromatographic peaks Abundance ratios and characteristic ion fragments were used for quantification, and peak area external standard method was used for quantification;

Among them, the liquid chromatography conditions are:

The chromatographic column adopts a chromatographic column with octadecylsilane bonded silica gel or octaalkylsilane bonded silica gel as filler;

ABThe mobile phase consists of mobile phase A and mobile phase B;

AAdopt formic acid-containing ammonium acetate aqueous solution or formic acid-containing ammonium formate aqueous solution as described mobile phase A;

BAdopt acetonitrile or methanol as described mobile phase B;

The elution mode is isocratic or gradient elution.

The beneficial effects of the present invention are:

N-N-The invention provides a method for distinguishing methamphetamine and N-isopropylbenzylamine. The method has strong specificity, high degree of separation, good precision, stability and reproducibility, high recovery rate, accurate results, and can be At the same time, the qualitative and quantitative analysis of these two compounds can effectively distinguish methamphetamine and its isomer N-isopropylbenzylamine in the actual case analysis involving the qualitative and quantitative analysis of methamphetamine. significant.

Detailed ways

N-Provided in the present invention is a method for analyzing methamphetamine and N-isopropylbenzylamine high performance liquid chromatography in series with mass spectrometry.

PFPC8C18PFPN-PFPN-m/z150.1>91.1m/z150.1>57.3C8C18C18The inventors explored PFP column, C8 column and C18 column for separation analysis. PFP column is a commonly used chromatographic column for the analysis of poisonous drugs at present, but the retention time of methamphetamine and N-isopropylbenzylamine in the PFP column is the same, so they cannot be effectively separated. Common m/z150.1>91.1, m/z150.1>57.3 ion pair, in the LC-MS analysis, the two cannot be distinguished, and it is very easy to misjudge; C8 column and C18 column were found during the test. The two can be effectively separated, but the separation effect of C18 column is better.

5m3.5m2.7m1.7mC181.7m2.7mComparing C18 columns with 5m, 3.5m, 2.7m and 1.7m particle size packings, the results show that the separation effect and detection sensitivity are better when using 1.7m and 2.7m particle size columns.

////--5mmol/L10mmol/L20mmol/L0.120mmol/L/20/80The mobile phase was optimized for methanol/water, acetonitrile/water, methanol/buffer, acetonitrile/buffer and other systems, among which the buffer system was tested with ammonium formate-formic acid and ammonium acetate-formic acid system, the concentrations were 5mmol/L and 10mmol/L, respectively. L, 20mmol/L, and finally determined to use 20mmol/L ammonium acetate aqueous solution/acetonitrile system containing 0.1% formic acid, isocratic elution or gradient elution with a volume ratio of 20/80, which has the best separation effect and detection sensitivity.

screening test

10LN-N-N-()N-N-Take 10 L of the test sample solution for analysis on a high performance liquid chromatography tandem mass spectrometer, first take the lowest concentration point for testing, and then gradually increase the test sample concentration according to the test results to obtain the best injection concentration. The blank control samples and positive control samples were tested simultaneously. If the characteristic ion pair of methamphetamine or N-isopropylbenzylamine does not appear in the blank sample, the characteristic ion pair of methamphetamine and N-isopropylbenzylamine appears in the positive control sample, and there is no methylamphetamine in the test sample. The characteristic ion pair of methamphetamine or N-isopropylbenzylamine, it can be determined that the test sample does not contain these two compounds; if the characteristics of methamphetamine or (and) N-isopropylbenzylamine appear in the test sample ion pair, it can be preliminarily determined that the sample contains methamphetamine or N-isopropylbenzylamine, or both compounds.

Qualitative confirmation test

N-(RSD<2.5)2After the screening is completed, further qualitative confirmation tests can be carried out, as follows: prepare single standard and mixed standard of methamphetamine and N-isopropylbenzylamine, inject the standard samples of the two compounds, and compare the two compounds respectively The retention time of the characteristic ion peak in the standard sample and the test sample, the two pairs of characteristic ion pairs and the abundance ratio of the two pairs of characteristic ion pairs, if the characteristic ion peak in the test sample is consistent with the standard sample characteristic ion peak retention time (RSD <2.5%), the two pairs of characteristic ion pairs are consistent, and the abundance ratio of the two pairs of characteristic ion pairs meets the error requirements in Table 2, it can be confirmed that the test sample contains the compound.

Claims (8)

translated from

1. A method for distinguishing methamphetamine from N-isopropylamine, comprising the steps of:
1) preparing a test sample solution;
2) injecting the sample solution into a high performance liquid chromatography tandem mass spectrometer for determination, selecting characteristic ion pairs and characteristic fragment ions, comparing the retention time of chromatographic peaks of the sample solution and a standard sample, determining the nature of the characteristic ion pairs, the abundance ratio of the characteristic ion pairs and the characteristic ion fragments, and quantifying by using a peak area external standard method;
wherein, the liquid phase chromatographic conditions are as follows:
the chromatographic column adopts octadecylsilane chemically bonded silica or octaalkylsilane chemically bonded silica as a filler;
the mobile phase consists of a mobile phase A and a mobile phase B;
adopting ammonium acetate aqueous solution containing formic acid or ammonium formate aqueous solution containing formic acid as the mobile phase A;
acetonitrile or methanol is adopted as the mobile phase B;
the elution mode is isocratic elution or gradient elution.
2. The method of claim 1, wherein: the particle size of the filler is 1.7-5 m.
3. The method of claim 2, wherein: the filler particle size was 1.7 m.
4. The method of claim 1, wherein: and the mobile phase A adopts 5-20 mmol/L ammonium acetate aqueous solution containing 0.1% formic acid or 5-20 mmol/L ammonium formate aqueous solution containing 0.1% formic acid.
5. The method of claim 1, wherein: the elution mode is isocratic elution, and the volume ratio of the mobile phase A to the mobile phase B is 20/80 or 30/70.
6. The method of claim 5, wherein: the flow rate is 0.2-0.6 mL/min, and the column temperature is 30-45 .
7. The method of claim 1, wherein: the mass spectrum detection adopts the following mass spectrum conditions:
electrospray positive ion mode (ESI +);
the detection mode is as follows: multiple reaction monitoring mode detection (MRM);
characteristic ion pair: the methamphetamine takes two pairs of ions with m/z150.1>119.1, m/z150.1>91.1 as characteristic ion pairs, and the N-isopropylbenzylamine takes two pairs of ions with m/z150.1>91.1, 150.1>58.1 as characteristic ion pairs;
characteristic ion fragment: characteristic fragment ions of methamphetamine are 119.1, 91.1 and 58.1, and characteristic fragment ions of N-isopropylbenzylamine are 91.1 and 58.1;
air curtain gas (CurtainGas, CUR)15 Psi; collisional gas (CollisionGas) Medium; spray voltage (ion spray voltage, IS) 5500V; temperature of atomization (TEM) 600 ; atomizing gas (IonSourceGas1)55 Psi; auxiliary gas (IonSourceGas2)65 Psi;
MRM mode ion pair parameters:
8. the method of claim 1, wherein: the preparation method of the sample solution comprises the following steps: taking a sample to be tested, ultrasonically dissolving the sample by using methanol as a solvent, and filtering the sample to obtain the product.
